Task 1
Copy the /etc/services file to your current working directory under the name services.
Task 2
Extract all comment lines (lines starting with #) from the services file and save them in a new file named services_comments.txt.
Task 3
Create a new file named services_wo_comments.txt that contains all the data from the services file but without any comments.
Task 4
Extract only the lines containing /udp from the file without comments and save them in services_udp.txt.
Task 5
Note: The assignment requires processing a file named "well-known-ports.txt", which was not previously created. To proceed, rename "services_wo_comments.txt" to "well-known-ports.txt".
Replace all forward slashes (/) with dashes (-) in the first 100 lines of well-known-ports.txt and save the result to 100-well-known-ports.txt.
Task 6
Create two files: doc1.txt containing department codes and locations (e.g., 10-IT-HQ) and doc2.txt containing employee IDs and names (e.g., 10-B.Thomas).
Task 7
Merge the contents of doc1.txt and doc2.txt into a single file named doc3.txt.
Task 8
Enter a set of commands to extract the unique values from the third field of doc3.txt file and store them in locations.txt file.
Task 9
Extend the previous command in order to count the unique values and store the result to the locations-count.txt file.
Task 10
Find all files in the /etc directory that are smaller than 200 bytes, sort them alphabetically by path, and save the list to small-etc-files.txt.
